<paragraph blockId="3.[801,1451,1260,1316]" pageId="3" pageNumber="74">
<emphasis box="[839,950,1260,1284]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="74">Etymology</emphasis>
. – The epithet 
<taxonomicName authorityName="F. J. Roldan, Carmona, Alzate &amp; J. S. Murillo. A. Habit" authorityYear="2021" box="[1117,1242,1260,1284]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Loranthaceae" genus="Aetanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Santalales" pageId="3" pageNumber="74" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alternifolius">
<emphasis box="[1117,1242,1260,1284]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="74">alternifolius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
refers to the phyllotaxy in mature shoots.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[801,1452,1356,1540]" pageId="3" pageNumber="74">
<emphasis box="[839,1090,1356,1380]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="74">Distribution and habitat</emphasis>
. – 
<taxonomicName authorityName="F. J. Roldan, Carmona, Alzate &amp; J. S. Murillo. A. Habit" authorityYear="2021" box="[1121,1349,1356,1380]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Loranthaceae" genus="Aetanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Santalales" pageId="3" pageNumber="74" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alternifolius">
<emphasis box="[1121,1349,1356,1380]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="74">Aetanthus alternifolius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known only from a single specimen collected in the municipality of California, in montane oak (
<taxonomicName authority="Bonpl." authorityName="Bonpl." box="[1098,1370,1420,1444]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="3" pageNumber="74" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="humboldtii">
<emphasis box="[1098,1291,1420,1444]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="74">Quercus humboldtii</emphasis>
Bonpl.
</taxonomicName>
) forests belonging to the surrounding area of the Páramo de Santurbán (
<collectingRegion box="[808,918,1484,1508]" country="Colombia" name="Santander" pageId="3" pageNumber="74">Santander</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[929,1037,1484,1508]" name="Colombia" pageId="3" pageNumber="74">Colombia</collectingCountry>
) close to 
<quantity box="[1138,1221,1484,1508]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.8" pageId="3" pageNumber="74" unit="m" value="2800.0">2800 m</quantity>
. Host is unknown for this species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[801,1452,1580,1668]" pageId="3" pageNumber="74">
<emphasis box="[839,942,1580,1604]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="74">Phenology</emphasis>
. – This species was collected with several inflorescences in anthesis and flower buds at the end of January. Fruits remain unknown.
</paragraph>
